<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>About - Movie Rental</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body {
      background-color: #f8f9fa;
    }
    .about-header {
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #0d6efd, #6610f2);
      color: white;
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
      border-radius: 0 0 1rem 1rem;
    }
    .tech-card {
      transition: transform 0.2s;
    }
    .tech-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-5px);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="about-header text-center mb-5">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">About Our Movie Rental System</h1>
      <p class="lead">A full-stack Node.js + MySQL project showcasing CRUD, authentication, and CI/CD deployment.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <main class="container mb-5">
    <div class="row g-5">
      <section class="col-md-9 mx-auto">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          This application replicates a movie rental system using the official <strong>Sakila MySQL sample database</strong>.  
          It demonstrates modern web development practices:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Server-side rendering with <strong>EJS</strong></li>
          <li>Repository/DAO pattern for database access</li>
          <li>Customer registration & login with password hashing</li>
          <li>Staff invitation and onboarding workflows</li>
          <li>Film CRUD with validation</li>
          <li>Bootstrap 5 styled forms and layouts</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Technologies Used</h2>
        <div class="row row-cols-1 row-cols-md-2 g-4">
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Backend</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>Node.js + Express.js</li>
                  <li>Repository pattern (callbacks)</li>
                  <li>Authentication & session handling</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Frontend</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>EJS templating engine</li>
                  <li>Bootstrap 5</li>
                  <li>Custom validation scripts</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Database</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>MySQL (Sakila sample schema)</li>
                  <li>Film, rental, staff, customer management</li>
                  <li>Address lookup with countries/cities</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col">
            <div class="card tech-card h-100 shadow-sm">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">Deployment</h5>
                <ul class="mb-0">
                  <li>Docker + Compose</li>
                  <li>CI/CD with GitHub Actions</li>
                  <li>Nginx reverse proxy</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Features by Version</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>v1</strong> – Basic movie listings</li>
          <li><strong>v2</strong> – Film CRUD (create, update, delete)</li>
          <li><strong>v3</strong> – Registration & login forms with DB integration</li>
          <li><strong>v4</strong> – Validation, error handling, Bootstrap styling</li>
          <li><strong>v5</strong> – Staff invitation & onboarding</li>
          <li><strong>v6</strong> – Customer & staff session authentication</li>
          <li><strong>v7</strong> – Rental management tracking</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Future Development</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Search & filter for films/customers</li>
          <li>Rental due dates & late fee system</li>
          <li>Public REST API</li>
          <li>Cypress end-to-end test coverage</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3">Source Code</h2>
        <p>
          View the project on GitHub:  
          <a href="https://github.com/s-kroonen/POC-Avans-KeuzeKompas" target="_blank">github.com/s-kroonen/POC-Avans-KeuzeKompas</a>
        </p>

        <% if (user && user.is_admin) { %>
          <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
            <strong>Admin Access:</strong> You are logged in as a staff member.  
            <a href="/admin" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary ms-2">Go to Admin Panel</a>
          </div>
        <% } %>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</body>
</html>